         <div>
            <head>30.5.1881 Montag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49097">Ascot</placeName> 30 May 1881
      Monday</p>
            <p>Today at dinner the Head<note type="reg">
                  <persName key="667">Sneyd-Kynnersley</persName>
               </note> after grace said
      &#x201e;Stop please. I am very grieved to hear that all the boys are not
      truthful here. <persName key="912">Blundell</persName> stand up. I find you have gone
      through a long course of deceit. ........ I have written to you father about it
      and asked him to come and see you. I can&#x2019;t have such a boy here. of
      course you shall be flogged but that is not the worse .... <persName key="913">Thomson ma.</persName> and <persName key="894">Olliver</persName> bring
      <persName key="912">Blundell</persName> up to my room&#x201c; Probably he will be expeled.
               <persName key="667">The head</persName> also spoke of certain half crowns which
               <persName key="912">Blundell</persName> had been anxious should be given to <persName key="914">Annie</persName> who was last term in charge of the cottage</p>
         </div>
